  <thing id="fAirKata" name="Air Kata" description="You movements speak to the winds.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Wis 13, Improved Unarmed Strike.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} As long as you fulfill the somatic components of a spell with the [air] subtype, you do not need to fulfill the verbal components. If you bypass the somatic component in some way (such as Still Spell), you must fulfill the verbal component normally." compset="Feat" summary="You movements speak to the winds." uniqueness="useronce">
